result.name: Genki Sushi

reviews.text:
Nice sushi restaurant with all kinds of sushi to choose. However the choice for Nigiri is limited,  especially for Tuna lovers.
Nice interiors, great trains to transport your sushi. The cost is that you don’t have lunch set here, only inside traditional sushi track style one.

Bear in mind that it would be very crowded on Saturdays or Public Holidays. Better come in non-holiday weekdays. Holidays should be best to watch Netflix at home rather than dine out.
Sushi train restaurant. Order via your own phone. Great experience especially for children. Yummy food selection. Definitely visit again.

They leveled up their ordering system where you will scan a Qcode using your phone, install the app, chose and order your food, then in a matter of minutes (or even in seconds) your food will be delivered to you on a mini train... Talk about enjoying your dining experience.
A bit cold in the restaurant. The soft bone chicken is a bit salty
it's okay for sushi not that expensive.

result.formatted_address: B105-B108, 4 - 30 Tai Pa St, Tsuen Wan, 香港
result.name: 元気寿司

reviews.text: 😌現年盛行素食，但元氣多年都未能跟上配合提供素食餐單😐可惜！
食物保持一貫水準 員工有禮貌 地方乾淨 不過唔知係咪因為比較早期轉新幹線 有啲車開始損壞 見過有架車行咗出嚟唔識行返入去 要職員幫手拎返入去 不過繁忙時間超多人 隔離同對面兩間舖頭 唔使等位 但係佢就好多人排隊 不過多人係一般元氣壽司都會係咁 如果你唔係會員 冇得遙控攞飛 基本上想食元氣壽司係極之難 建議喺一般食飯嘅時間早一個鐘頭 已來攞定位
8號風球下元氣員工仍緊守崗位服務大家，謝謝!

炸雞超差，送來時不熱，分量少得可憐
又大件不脆口
沒有給沙律醬
環境有點污糟 上手食客的位置沒清潔好
好味 但係啲食物黎得慢咗啲

reviews.text: Good shopping mall with a slightly upscale tint to it. Has nice open areas throughout and several floors to explore. Additionally, it does have several styles of cuisine and snacks on location, which makes it very good for just casual hanging out if you're in Tsuen Wan.
Shopping mall with a good variety of shops and restaurants, playground area good for kids.
Shop and restuarant are so great but car parking is poor

medium sized shopping centre but there are a number of this type of shopping centres that are connected by flyovers here. hence, it is a part of a huge shopping complex in the area. recommended if you would like to spend an afternoon here. you never run out of shopping options.
mon to fri parking reasonable
